text: Val-de-Livenne is a commune. It is found in the region Nouvelle-Aquitaine in the Gironde department in the southwest of France. The municipality was created on 1 January 2019 and consists of the former communes of Saint- Caprais-de-Blaye (the seat) and Marcillac.Arrêté préfectoral 1 October 2018 == References == Category:2019 establishments in France Category:Communes in Gironde
title: Val-de-Livenne
